{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29065324-3c5d-45fb-8899-0d7932169a22","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```jsonc\n// Change\n\"version\": \"10.0.100\"\n// To\n\"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0\n# To\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\nAfter updating, install the .NET 11 SDK, then run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to catch any breaking API changes. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking changes relevant to your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e637c005-0f6d-4535-a380-3b6a231f36d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I don't need to explore any codebase since they're describing their setup generically.\n\nHere's what they need to update:\n\n1. **`.csproj`** — Change `<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>` → `<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>`\n2. **`global.json`** — Change SDK version from `10.0.100` → `11.0.100`\n\n\n3. **`Dockerfile`** — Update the base images from `aspnet:10.0` and `sdk:10.0` to their `11.0` equivalents.","outputTokens":488},"id":"413480cd-6e11-4446-9f5a-44341d710ab7","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:40.382Z","parentId":"dddd7cca-2e17-4bd4-b743-21f959aa7817"}
